output.map_title: Map to show the number of graduates of all subjects now working in Education who are current living in each region 3 years after graduation, male and female Level 7 (research) graduates from English HEIs, APs and FECs, 2018/19 tax year.
output.maptext:
For Level 7 (research) graduates of all subjects in the Education industry 3 years after graduation, the region that saw the highest number of students
                    studying there was East of England . The region with the lowest number of students studying
                    there was East Midlands . The region with the highest number of graduates living
                    there 3 years after graduation was South East  and the region with the
                    least graduates living there was North East .
output.maptext2:
For Level 7 (research) graduates of all subjects in the Education industry, the region with the highest proportionate increase in graduates who studied there compared to living
                    there 3 years after graduation is South East , where the number of
                    graduates increased by 34.3 %. The region with the largest
                    decrease is East Midlands where the number of graduates decreased by 209.8 %.
